The Vice President, Mike Pence, delivered remarks at a gathering to pay tribute to Immigrations and Customs Enforcement (ICE) and Customs and Border Protection (CBP). He expressed gratitude to the officers for their efforts in securing the borders and enforcing laws. Pence highlighted the achievements of CBP, including apprehending dangerous criminals and preventing known or suspected terrorists from entering the country. He also praised ICE for arresting criminal illegal immigrants and rescuing victims of child exploitation. Pence assured the law enforcement officers that they have the support of the American people and President Donald Trump, who has increased funding for border security and begun construction of the border wall. He emphasized that the administration will continue to provide resources and respect to these agencies. Pence concluded by thanking the officers for their service and offering prayers for their safety.